129 /*
130  UnsavedStream encapsulates a dictionary's modified stream data before it is
131  written to a file. The raw bytes are in the provided data_store. If "m_alreadyCompressed"
132  is true, the data is presumed to be unfiltered, and when it is requested in filtered
133  form the filters/decode parameters as described by the attached dictionary are applied.
134 
135  If false, the data is presumed to be filtered already. The length key is the length of the
136  _uncompressed_ data, and the filter keys are ignored. At save time the /Length key is rewritten
137  and the data is compressed then.
138 */
139 class UnsavedStream
140 {
141  bool m_alreadyCompressed;
142  t4::data_store m_ds;
143 
144 public:
145  UnsavedStream( void ) = default;
146 
147  UnsavedStream( bool alreadyCompressed, t4::data_store ds )
148  : m_alreadyCompressed( alreadyCompressed ),
149  m_ds( std::move( ds ) )
150  {
151  tetraphilia_assert( m_ds );
152  }
153 
154  explicit operator bool( void ) const { return bool( m_ds ); }
155 
156  bool AlreadyCompressed( void ) const { return m_alreadyCompressed; }
157  t4::data_store const& GetDataStore( void ) const { return m_ds; }
158 };

171 template<typename object_traits>
172 struct DictionaryObj
173 {
174  typedef typename object_traits::app_traits app_traits;
175  typedef typename app_traits::pdf_traits::int_type int_type;
176  typedef typename app_traits::file_system_traits::file_size_type file_size_type;
177  typedef typename object_traits::obj_impl_stack_type obj_impl_stack_type;
178  typedef typename t4::sptr<IndirectObject<app_traits>> ido_ptr_type;
179 
180  typedef TransientAllocator<app_traits> allocator_type;
181 
182  DictionaryObj( TransientHeap<app_traits>& heap, file_size_type uniqueKeyNum, IndirectObject<app_traits>* ido, is_dictionary is_dictionary, is_parsing_dictionary is_parsing_dictionary = is_parsing_dictionary::no )
183  : /*
184  * For newly created dict or array objects, we are passing m_containerObjNum as -1
185  * to the m_storeKey. This is to uniquely identify them with the pos (which is a
186  * running counter)
187  */
188  m_streamStartPos( 0 ),
189  m_ido( ido ),
190  m_stack( allocator_type( heap ) )
191  {
192  init( is_dictionary );
193  SetParsingDictionary( is_parsing_dictionary );
194 
195  m_storeKeyMap[0] = StoreKey( uniqueKeyNum, -1 );
196  object_traits::SetStackIDO(m_stack, m_ido);
197  }
198 
199  DictionaryObj( TransientHeap<app_traits>& heap, const StoreKey& storeKey, IndirectObject<app_traits>* ido, is_dictionary is_dictionary, is_parsing_dictionary is_parsing_dictionary )
200  : m_streamStartPos( 0 ),
201  m_ido( ido ),
202  m_stack( allocator_type( heap ) )
203  {
204  init( is_dictionary );
205  SetParsingDictionary( is_parsing_dictionary );
206 
207  m_storeKeyMap[0] = storeKey;
208  object_traits::SetStackIDO(m_stack, m_ido);
209  }
210 
211  /*
212  Create a temporary DictionaryObj. Temporary DictionaryObjs have unique StoreKeys using
213  the same mechanism as modified objects.
214  */
215  DictionaryObj( const DictionaryObj& dictToCopy, TransientHeap<app_traits>& heap, file_size_type uniqueKeyNum, IndirectObject<app_traits>* ido, is_dictionary is_dictionary )
216  : m_streamStartPos( dictToCopy.m_streamStartPos ),
217  m_ido( ido ),
218  m_stack( allocator_type( heap ) )
219  {
220  init( is_dictionary );
221  SetParsingDictionary( is_dictionary? is_parsing_dictionary::yes : is_parsing_dictionary::no );
222 
223  m_storeKeyMap[0] = StoreKey( uniqueKeyNum, -1 );
224  object_traits::SetStackIDO(m_stack, m_ido);
225  if(dictToCopy.IsUnsavedStream())
226  SetUnsavedStream( dictToCopy.GetUnsavedStream() );
227 
228  typedef typename obj_impl_stack_type::const_iterator const_iterator;
229  const_iterator it = dictToCopy.m_stack.begin();
230  const_iterator end = dictToCopy.m_stack.end();
231 
232  VersionResolver<object_traits, typename object_traits::obj_elem_type> resolver;
233 
234  while ( it != end )
235  {
236  const ObjectImpl<object_traits>& objImpl = resolver(*it);
237  m_stack.Push( *DeepCopy( heap, objImpl, uniqueKeyNum, ido ) );
238  ++it;
239  }
240 
241  SetParsingDictionary( is_parsing_dictionary::no );
242  }
243 
244  DictionaryObj( const DictionaryObj& rhs, TransientHeap<app_traits>& heap, is_dictionary is_dictionary )
245  : m_streamStartPos( rhs.m_streamStartPos ),
246  m_ido( rhs.m_ido ),
247  m_stack( allocator_type( heap ), rhs.m_stack.size() + 1 )
248  {
249  init( is_dictionary );
250  SetParsingDictionary( is_dictionary? is_parsing_dictionary::yes : is_parsing_dictionary::no );
251 
252  m_storeKeyMap[0] = rhs.GetStoreKey();
253  object_traits::SetStackIDO(m_stack, m_ido);
254  if(rhs.IsUnsavedStream())
255  SetUnsavedStream( rhs.GetUnsavedStream() );
256 
257  typedef typename obj_impl_stack_type::const_iterator const_iterator;
258  const_iterator it = rhs.m_stack.begin();
259  const_iterator end = rhs.m_stack.end();
260 
261  VersionResolver<object_traits, typename object_traits::obj_elem_type> resolver;
262 
263  while ( it != end )
264  {
265  const ObjectImpl<object_traits>& objImpl = resolver(*it);
266  m_stack.Push( *DeepCopy( heap, objImpl ) );
267  ++it;
268  }
269 
270  SetParsingDictionary( is_parsing_dictionary::no );
271  }
272 
273  bool HasStream( void ) const
274  {
275  return IsDiskStream() || IsUnsavedStream();
276  }
277 
278  bool IsUnsavedStream() const
279  {
280  if (!m_memBufMap.empty())
281  {
282  if (((m_memBufMap.cbegin())->first) <= GetTransactionNumber())
283  return true;
284  }
285  return false;
286  }
287 
288  bool IsDiskStream() const
289  {
290  // Checking m_stream​StartPos ​!= 0 to ensure that 'HasStream' method
291  // does not return true even for the cases where stream does not exist at all.
292  return (!IsUnsavedStream() && m_streamStartPos != 0);
293  }
294 
295  void SetUnsavedStream( UnsavedStream const& us )
296  {
297  auto tn = m_ido->IsTemporary() ? 0 : GetTransactionNumber();
298  m_memBufMap[tn] = us;
299  }

301  void SerializeDictionary( typename data_io::data_io_detail::OutputStream* stream ) const
302  {
303  stream->write("<<", 2);
304 
305  VersionResolver<object_traits, typename object_traits::obj_elem_type> resolver;
306 
307  typename obj_impl_stack_type::const_iterator it = m_stack.begin();
308  while( it != m_stack.end() )
309  {
310  const ObjectImpl<object_traits>& objImpl = resolver(*it);
311  objImpl.SerializeObjectImpl( stream );
312  ++it;
313  }
314 
315  stream->write(">>", 2);
316  }
317 
318  void SerializeArray( typename data_io::data_io_detail::OutputStream* stream ) const
319  {
320  stream->write("[", 1);
321 
322  VersionResolver<object_traits, typename object_traits::obj_elem_type> resolver;
323 
324  typename obj_impl_stack_type::const_iterator it = m_stack.begin();
325  while( it != m_stack.end() )
326  {
327  const ObjectImpl<object_traits>& objImpl = resolver(*it);
328  objImpl.SerializeObjectImpl( stream );
329  ++it;
330  }
331 
332  stream->write("]", 1);
333  }

345  void SetStoreKey(const StoreKey& storeKey)
346  {
347  m_storeKeyMap[GetTransactionNumber()] = storeKey;
348  }
349 
350  const StoreKey& GetStoreKey() const
351  {
352  auto currentTransactionNumber = GetTransactionNumber();
353  auto lIter = m_storeKeyMap.lower_bound(currentTransactionNumber); // lIter->first >= pTransactionNumber
354 
355  if (lIter != m_storeKeyMap.end() && lIter->first == currentTransactionNumber)
356  {
357  return lIter->second;
358  }
359  else
360  {
361  --lIter;
362  return lIter->second;
363  }
364  }
365 
366  void DropTransactions(size_t pTransactionNumber)
367  {
368  auto lIter = m_memBufMap.lower_bound(pTransactionNumber); // lIter->first >= pTransactionNumber
369  m_memBufMap.erase(lIter, m_memBufMap.end());
370 
371  auto lIterKey = m_storeKeyMap.lower_bound(pTransactionNumber);
372  m_storeKeyMap.erase(lIterKey, m_storeKeyMap.end());
373  }
374 
375  bool HasVersion(size_t pTransactionNumber) const
376  {
377  return (m_memBufMap.find(pTransactionNumber) != m_memBufMap.end());
378  }
379 
380  // if this is a dictionary (not an array) then this is set to non-zero if this is a stream in the PDF - not yet edited in memory,
381  // and zero if it is a non-stream dictionary.
382  // if this is a stream edited in memory, then this value is zero as well. In that case m_memoryDataStore is valid.
383  // if this is an array (not a dictionary) then this value is undefined
384  file_size_type m_streamStartPos;
385 
386  UnsavedStream const& GetUnsavedStream() const
387  {
388  if (!IsUnsavedStream())
389  throw t4::corrupt_data();
390 
391  auto currentTransactionNumber = GetTransactionNumber();
392  auto lIter = m_memBufMap.lower_bound(currentTransactionNumber); // lIter->first >= pTransactionNumber
393 
394  if (lIter != m_memBufMap.end() && lIter->first == currentTransactionNumber)
395  {
396  return lIter->second;
397  }
398  else
399  {
400  --lIter;
401  return lIter->second;
402  }
403  }
404 
405  // No-op for the default case, used in the StoreObjTraits template specialization
406  void SetParsingDictionary( is_parsing_dictionary is_parsing_dictionary ) {}
407 
408 private:
409 
410  // No-op for the default case, used in the StoreObjTraits template specialization
411  void init( is_dictionary is_dictionary ) {}
412 
413  size_t GetTransactionNumber() const
414  {
415  return pdf::transactions::TransactionManager::GetCurrentTransactionNumber();
416  }
417 
418  IndirectObject<app_traits>* m_ido;
419  obj_impl_stack_type m_stack;
420 
421  t4::map<size_t, UnsavedStream> m_memBufMap;
422  t4::map<size_t, StoreKey> m_storeKeyMap;
423 };

425 struct Reference
426 {
427  using int_type = t4::app_traits::pdf_traits::int_type;

429  Reference( void ) {}
430  Reference( int_type objNum, int_type generation ) : m_objNum(objNum), m_generation(generation) {}
431 
432  void SerializeReference( typename tetraphilia::data_io::data_io_detail::OutputStream* stream ) const
433  {
434  WriteSpace( stream );
435  WriteIntType( stream, m_objNum );
436  WriteSpace( stream );
437  WriteIntType( stream, m_generation );
438  WriteSpace( stream );
439  stream->write( "R", 1 );
440  }
441 
442 #ifdef _DEBUG
443  // Used for printing object graph (while debugging)
444  void print() const
445  {
446  printf("%d %d R", m_objNum, m_generation);
447  }
448 #endif
449 
450  int_type m_objNum;
451  int_type m_generation;
452 
453  friend std::ostream& operator<<( std::ostream& stm, Reference const& ths )
454  {
455  return stm << ths.m_objNum << " " << ths.m_generation << " R";
456  }
457 };

459 inline bool operator==( const Reference& lhs, const Reference& rhs )

474 /*
475  This union/struct is separated out from ObjectImpl because of a bug in gcc 2.95 which causes the compiler
476  to crash if you declare a union inside of a templatized struct. Simply moving the declaraion out
477  is enough to get around the bug.
478 */
479 template<typename object_traits>
480 union ObjData
481 {
482  typedef typename object_traits::app_traits app_traits;
483 
484  typedef typename app_traits::pdf_traits::real_type real_type;
485  typedef typename real_services::RealTypeHelper<real_type>::static_type static_real_type;
486 
487  typename app_traits::pdf_traits::int_type intRep; // also used for bool
488  static_real_type realRep;
489  typename app_traits::pdf_traits::large_int_type* largeIntRep;
490  StringObj* nameAndStringRep;
491  DictionaryObj<object_traits>* dictAndArrayRep;
492  Reference* refRep;
493 };

501  typedef typename app_traits::pdf_traits::large_int_type large_int_type;
502  typedef typename app_traits::file_system_traits::file_size_type file_size_type;
503 
504  ObjectType type;
505  ObjData<object_traits> u;
506

582 
583  void SetLargeIntValue( const large_int_type& lval );
584  /*
585  * Allow the underlying original type to get changed from Integer to LargeInteger.
586  * This is because, when the actual type is integer with a value of 1000, the user will be
587  * able to read it as LargeInteger but at the writing time we will raise an exception because of
588  * the type mis-match.
589  * The types integer/real/largeinteger are very much related and can be interchangably used to
590  * represent something like 1000. If the conversion is not allowed, Parser and the Writer may
591  * need lot of unwanted code to handle the conversion so that we don't raise an exception at this point.
592  * The conversion is allowed only from Integer to LargeInteger or Real and not vice-versa.
593  */
594  void ForceSetLargeIntValue( large_int_type* lval );
595 
596  file_size_type FileSizeValue( void ) const;
597 
598  file_size_type FileSizeValue_NoTypeCheck( void ) const
599  {
600  if ( type == kObjectTypeInteger )
601  return t4::convert<file_size_type>( u.intRep );
602  tetraphilia_assert( type == kObjectTypeLargeInteger );
603  return t4::convert<file_size_type>( *u.largeIntRep );
604  }
605 
606  typename app_traits::pdf_traits::real_type RealValue( void ) const;

611  return real_services::PinToReal( ArgType<typename app_traits::pdf_traits::real_type>(), u.intRep );
612  tetraphilia_assert( type == kObjectTypeReal );
613  return u.realRep;
614  }

653  size_t GetCachedSize() const
654  {
655  size_t sz = sizeof (*this);
656  if (!std::is_trivially_destructible<ObjectImpl>::value)
657  {
658  switch (type)
659  {
660  case kObjectTypeString:
661  case kObjectTypeName:
662  sz += t4::ptr_size(u.nameAndStringRep);
663  break;
664  case kObjectTypeDictionary:
665  case kObjectTypeArray:
666  sz += t4::ptr_size(u.dictAndArrayRep);
667  break;
668  case kObjectTypeReference:
669  sz += t4::ptr_size(u.refRep);
670  break;
671  default: // quiets gcc compiler warning about enumeration types not being handled in a switch statement
672  break;
673  }
674  }
675  return sz;
676  }

807 template<typename Rng>
808 std::enable_if_t<t4::is_range_of_value<Rng, const char>::value,
809 void> SerializeHexString( data_io::data_io_detail::OutputStream* stream, Rng&& chars )
810 {
811  const static char hexDigits[] = "0123456789ABCDEF";
812  stream->write("<", 1);
813  for ( auto ch : chars )
814  {
815  auto c = static_cast<unsigned char>( ch );
816  stream->write(&(hexDigits[c >> 4]), 1);
817  stream->write(&(hexDigits[c & 0xF]), 1);
818  }
819  stream->write(">", 1);
820 }
821 
822 template<typename Rng>
823 std::enable_if_t<t4::is_range_of_value<Rng, const char>::value,
824 void> SerializeString( data_io::data_io_detail::OutputStream* stream, Rng&& chars )
825 {
826  stream->write("(", 1);
827 
828  for ( auto ch : chars )
829  {
830  auto c = static_cast<unsigned char>( ch );
831  if (c == '\r')
832  stream->write("\\r", 2);
833  else if (c == '\n')
834  stream->write("\\n", 2);
835  else if (c == '\\')
836  {
837  stream->write("\\", 1);
838  stream->write(&c, 1);
839  }
840  else if (c == '(')
841  stream->write("\\(", 2);
842  else if (c == ')')
843  stream->write("\\)", 2);
844  else
845  stream->write(&c, 1);
846  }
847 
848  stream->write(")", 1);
849 }
850 
851 template<typename object_traits>
852 void ObjectImpl<object_traits>::SerializeObjectImpl( data_io::data_io_detail::OutputStream* stream ) const
853 {
854  switch (type)
855  {
856  case kObjectTypeNull:
857  {
858  stream->write( " null", 5 );
859  break;
860  }
861  case kObjectTypeBool:
862  {
863  if( u.intRep != 0)
864  stream->write( " true", 5 );
865  else
866  stream->write( " false", 6 );
867  break;
868  }
869  case kObjectTypeInteger:
870  {
871  WriteSpace( stream );
872  WriteIntType( stream, u.intRep );
873  break;
874  }
875  case kObjectTypeReal:
876  {
877  WriteSpace( stream );
878  WriteRealType( stream, u.realRep );
879  break;
880  }
881  case kObjectTypeName:
882  {
883  const StringObj* strObj = u.nameAndStringRep;
884  const static char hexDigits[] = "0123456789ABCDEF";
885  unsigned char c = 0;
886  size_t index = 0;
887  size_t len = strObj->size();
888 
889  stream->write("/", 1);
890 
891  while (index < len)
892  {
893  c = static_cast<unsigned char>( strObj->data()[index] );
894  /* Using the 2-digit hexadecimal code, preceded by number sign character (#), for representing certain characters as suggested by the PDF Spec. */
895  if (c < 0x21 || c > 0x7E ||
896  (Parser::m_ByteTypes[c] & (Parser::kWhiteSpace | Parser::kDelimiter | Parser::kLineEnd))
897  || c == '%' || c == ')' || c == '>' || c == '#')
898  {
899  stream->write("#", 1);
900  stream->write(&(hexDigits [c >> 4]), 1);
901  stream->write(&(hexDigits [c & 0xF]), 1);
902  }
903  else
904  stream->write(&c, 1);
905  ++index;
906  }
907  break;
908  }
909  case kObjectTypeString:
910  {
911  const StringObj* strObj = u.nameAndStringRep;
912  auto rng = ranges::make_span( strObj->data(), strObj->data() + strObj->size() );
913  if(strObj->IsHexFormat())
914  SerializeHexString( stream, rng );
915  else
916  SerializeString( stream, rng );
917  break;
918  }
919  case kObjectTypeArray:
920  u.dictAndArrayRep->SerializeArray( stream );
921  break;
922  case kObjectTypeDictionary:
923  u.dictAndArrayRep->SerializeDictionary( stream );
924  break;
925  case kObjectTypeReference:
926  u.refRep->SerializeReference( stream );
927  break;
928  case kObjectTypeLargeInteger:
929  {
930  WriteSpace( stream );
931  WriteIntType( stream, *u.largeIntRep );
932  break;
933  }
934  }
935 }

937 /*
938  transient_heap-based object that provides stores a set of:
939 
940  tuple<transaction #, ido_ptr, versioner*>
941 
942  ...where the actual internal representation is a sequence
943  of maps using the above key types (terminating in a set<versioner*>).
944  In other words, the above representation is stored using:
945 
946  map<transaction #, map<ido_ptr, set<versioner*>>>
947 
948  Utility functions for iterating through all specific ido ptr/versioner pairs based
949  on transaction number are provided.
950 */
951 template<typename app_traits>
952 class IDOVersionCounter
953 {
954  using object_traits = StoreObjTraits<app_traits>;
955  using versioner = ObjectImplVersioner<object_traits>;
956  using indirect_object = IndirectObject<app_traits>;
957  using ido_ptr = t4::sptr<indirect_object>;
958 
959  using versioner_set = t4::transient_set<versioner*>;
960  using submap = t4::transient_map<ido_ptr, versioner_set>; // maps ido_ptr -> versioner_set
961  using map = t4::transient_map<size_t, submap>; // maps transaction number -> submap
962 
963  t4::transient_heap& m_heap;
964  map m_map;
965 
966 public:
967  IDOVersionCounter( t4::transient_heap& heap )
968  : m_heap( heap ),
969  m_map( t4::transient_allocator<std::pair<size_t, submap>>( heap ) )
970  {}
971 
972  /*
973  Call func(versioner*, ido_ptr) for each entry at the specified transaction #.
974  */
975  template<typename F>
976  void ApplyToAllEntriesAtVersion(size_t transactionNumber, F&& func, bool erase)
977  {
978  auto it = m_map.find( transactionNumber );
979  if ( it != m_map.end() )
980  {
981  for_each_submap( it->second, std::forward<F>( func ) );
982  if ( erase )
983  m_map.erase( it );
984  }
985  }
986 
987  /*
988  Call func(versioner*, ido_ptr) for each entry at or after the specified transaction #.
989  */
990  template<typename F>
991  void ApplyToAllEntriesBeyondVersion(size_t transactionNumber, F&& func, bool erase)
992  {
993  auto first = m_map.find( transactionNumber );
994  for ( auto it = first; it != m_map.end(); ++it )
995  for_each_submap( it->second, std::forward<F>( func ) );
996  if ( erase )
997  m_map.erase( first, m_map.end() );
998  }
999 
1000  /*
1001  Call func(versioner*, ido_ptr) for each entry before the specified transaction #.
1002  */
1003  template<typename F>
1004  void ApplyToAllEntriesBeforeVersion(size_t transactionNumber, F&& func, bool erase)
1005  {
1006  auto last = m_map.find( transactionNumber );
1007  for ( auto it = m_map.begin(); it != last; ++it )
1008  for_each_submap( it->second, std::forward<F>( func ) );
1009  if ( erase )
1010  m_map.erase( m_map.begin(), last );
1011  }
1012 
1013  void Erase( size_t transactionNumber, versioner* v, ido_ptr const& p )
1014  {
1015  auto vsp = get_versioner_set_pointer( transactionNumber, p );
1016  if ( vsp )
1017  vsp->erase( v );
1018  }
1019 
1020  void Insert( size_t transactionNumber, versioner* v, ido_ptr const& p )
1021  {
1022  auto& vsp = get_versioner_set( false, transactionNumber, p );
1023  vsp.insert( v );
1024  }
1025 
1026  bool Empty( void ) const { return m_map.empty(); }
1027 
1028 private:
1029  template<typename F>
1030  void for_each_submap( submap& sm, F&& func )
1031  {
1032  for ( auto& kv : sm )
1033  for_each_versioner( kv.second, std::forward<F>( func ), kv.first );
1034  }
1035 
1036  template<typename F>
1037  void for_each_versioner( versioner_set& vs, F&& func, ido_ptr const& ido )
1038  {
1039  using namespace t4::literals;
1040  for ( auto const& v : vs )
1041  func( v, ido );
1042  }
1043 
1044  submap& get_submap( bool assertExists, size_t transactionNumber )
1045  {
1046  auto result = m_map.emplace( transactionNumber, submap( t4::transient_allocator<std::pair<size_t, submap>>( m_heap ) ) );
1047  assert( !assertExists || !result.second );
1048  return result.first->second;
1049  }
1050 
1051  versioner_set& get_versioner_set( bool assertExists, size_t transactionNumber, ido_ptr const& p )
1052  {
1053  auto& sm = get_submap( assertExists, transactionNumber );
1054  auto result = sm.emplace( p, versioner_set( t4::transient_allocator<versioner*>( m_heap ) ) );
1055  assert( !assertExists || !result.second );
1056  return result.first->second;
1057  }
1058 
1059  submap* get_submap_pointer( size_t transactionNumber )
1060  {
1061  auto it = m_map.find( transactionNumber );
1062  return ( it != m_map.end() ) ? &it->second : nullptr;
1063  }
1064 
1065  versioner_set* get_versioner_set_pointer( size_t transactionNumber, ido_ptr const& p )
1066  {
1067  auto sm = get_submap_pointer( transactionNumber );
1068  if ( sm )
1069  {
1070  auto it = sm->find( p );
1071  return ( it != sm->end() ) ? &it->second : nullptr;
1072  }
1073 
1074  return {};
1075  }
1076 };

1130  typedef t4::set<smart_ptr_type, CompareIDOPtr<app_traits>> ido_set_type;
1131 
1132  ido_set_type GetDirtyObjSet(size_t pTransactionNumber)
1133  {
1134  tetraphilia_assert(m_tempMultiMap.empty());
1135 
1136  ido_set_type lSet;
1137 
1138  if(pTransactionNumber != 0)
1139  {
1140  auto lFunction = [&lSet] (const ObjectImplVersioner<object_traits>* pVersioner, const smart_ptr_type& pIDO)
1141  {
1142  lSet.emplace(pIDO);
1143  };
1144 
1145  ApplyFuncToAllEntriesBeforeVersion(pTransactionNumber + 1, lFunction, false);
1146  }
1147 
1148  return lSet;
1149  }

1151  /* Purges all ObjectImpls created at or after version pTransactionNumber */
1152  void DropTransactions(size_t pTransactionNumber)
1153  {
1154  tetraphilia_assert(pTransactionNumber != 0);
1155  tetraphilia_assert(m_tempMultiMap.empty());
1156 
1157  auto lFunction = [pTransactionNumber] (ObjectImplVersioner<object_traits>* pVersioner, const smart_ptr_type& pIDO)
1158  {
1159  pVersioner->DropTransactions(pTransactionNumber);
1160  };
1161 
1162  ApplyFuncToAllEntriesBeyondVersion(pTransactionNumber, lFunction, true);
1163  }
1164 
1165  void PromoteTempEntries(const smart_ptr_type& pIDO)
1166  {
1167  auto lIter = m_tempMultiMap.find(pIDO.get()), lEndIter = m_tempMultiMap.end();
1168  while(lIter != lEndIter)
1169  {
1170  if(lIter->first != pIDO.get())
1171  break;
1172 
1173  Insert(lIter->second.second, lIter->second.first, pIDO);
1174  m_tempMultiMap.erase(lIter++);
1175  }
1176  }

1179  void Insert(size_t pTransactionNumber, ObjectImplVersioner<object_traits>* pObjectImplVersioner, const smart_ptr_type& pIDO)

1182  tetraphilia_assert(!pIDO->IsTemporary());
1183  m_idoVersionCounter.Insert( pTransactionNumber, pObjectImplVersioner, pIDO );
1184  }

1186  void Insert(size_t pTransactionNumber, ObjectImplVersioner<object_traits>* pObjectImplVersioner, IndirectObject<app_traits>& pIDO)
1187  {
1188  tetraphilia_assert(pObjectImplVersioner->HasVersion(pTransactionNumber));
1189  tetraphilia_assert(!pIDO.IsTemporary());
1190 
1191  m_tempMultiMap.emplace(std::piecewise_construct, std::forward_as_tuple(&pIDO), std::forward_as_tuple(pObjectImplVersioner, pTransactionNumber));
1192  }
1193 
1194  void Erase(size_t pTransactionNumber, ObjectImplVersioner<object_traits>* pObjectImplVersioner, const smart_ptr_type& pIDO)
1195  {

1197  }
1198 
1199  void Erase(size_t pTransactionNumber, ObjectImplVersioner<object_traits>* pObjectImplVersioner, IndirectObject<app_traits>& pIDO)
1200  {
1201  auto lIter = m_tempMultiMap.find(&pIDO);
1202  auto lEndIter = m_tempMultiMap.end();
1203 
1204  tetraphilia_assert(lIter != lEndIter);
1205 
1206  for(; lIter != lEndIter; ++lIter)
1207  {
1208  tetraphilia_assert(lIter->first == &pIDO);
1209 
1210  if(lIter->second.first == pObjectImplVersioner && lIter->second.second == pTransactionNumber)
1211  {
1212  m_tempMultiMap.erase(lIter);
1213  break;
1214  }
1215  }
1216  }

1221  // Instead, we temporarily make the entry into m_tempMultiMap and later on promote these to m_idoVersionCounter.
1222

1229  t4::transient_allocator<std::pair<const IndirectObject<app_traits>* const, std::pair<ObjectImplVersioner<object_traits>*, size_t>>>> m_tempMultiMap;
1230 };

1240 class ObjectImplVersioner : public boost::noncopyable
1241 {
1242  typedef typename object_traits::app_traits app_traits;
1243  typedef TransientHeap<app_traits> heap_type;
1244  typedef t4::transient_allocator<std::pair<const size_t, ObjectImplVersioner<object_traits>*>> allocator_type;
1245  typedef VersionedStack<app_traits> stack_type;
1246  typedef typename app_traits::pdf_traits::large_int_type large_int_type;
1247  typedef IndirectObject<app_traits> ido_type;
1248  typedef typename t4::sptr<ido_type> smart_ptr_type;
1249

1251 
1252 public:
1253  ObjectImplVersioner(heap_type& heap, bool pInitWithEmptyObject)
1254  : m_heap(heap)
1255  , m_stack(nullptr)
1256  , m_allocator(m_heap)
1257  , m_onlyMember( nullptr )
1258  , m_map(std::less<size_t>(), m_allocator)
1259  {
1260  if(pInitWithEmptyObject)
1261  Insert(0, smart_ptr_type());
1262  }
1263 
1264  template<typename... Args>
1265  explicit ObjectImplVersioner(heap_type& heap, ido_type* ido, Args&&... pArgs)
1266  : m_heap(heap)
1267  , m_stack(nullptr)
1268  , m_allocator(m_heap)
1269  , m_onlyMember( nullptr )
1270  , m_map(std::less<size_t>(), m_allocator)
1271  {
1272  if(!ido)
1273  {
1274  Insert(GetTransactionNumber(), smart_ptr_type(), std::forward<Args>(pArgs)...);
1275  }
1276  else
1277  {
1278  auto transactionNumber = ido->IsTemporary() ? 0 : GetTransactionNumber();
1279  smart_ptr_type lSharedPtr = ido->GetStore()->GetIDOSharedPtr(*ido);
1280  if(lSharedPtr.get())
1281  Insert(transactionNumber, lSharedPtr, std::forward<Args>(pArgs)...);
1282  else
1283  Insert(transactionNumber, *ido, std::forward<Args>(pArgs)...);
1284  }
1285  }
1286 
1287  template<typename... Args>
1288  explicit ObjectImplVersioner(stack_type& stack, ido_type* ido, Args&&... pArgs)
1289  : m_heap(stack.GetHeap())
1290  , m_stack( &stack )
1291  , m_allocator(m_heap)
1292  , m_onlyMember( nullptr )
1293  , m_map(std::less<size_t>(), m_allocator)
1294  {
1295  if(!ido)
1296  {
1297  Insert(GetTransactionNumber(), smart_ptr_type(), std::forward<Args>(pArgs)...);
1298  }
1299  else
1300  {
1301  auto transactionNumber = ido->IsTemporary() ? 0 : GetTransactionNumber();
1302  smart_ptr_type lSharedPtr = ido->GetStore()->GetIDOSharedPtr(*ido);
1303  if(lSharedPtr.get())
1304  Insert(transactionNumber, lSharedPtr, std::forward<Args>(pArgs)...);
1305  else
1306  Insert(transactionNumber, *ido, std::forward<Args>(pArgs)...);
1307  }
1308  }

1355  /* Returns the ObjectImpl created at transaction number pTransactionNumber */
1356  const ObjectImpl<object_traits>& GetVersion(size_t pTransactionNumber) const
1357  {
1358  if ( m_onlyMember )
1359  {
1360  tetraphilia_assert( m_map.begin()->first <= pTransactionNumber );
1361  return *m_onlyMember;
1362  }
1363 
1364  const auto lIter = m_map.find(pTransactionNumber);
1365 
1366  tetraphilia_assert(lIter != m_map.end());
1367 
1368  return lIter->second;
1369  }

1371  /* Returns the ObjectImpl created at the highest transaction number <= pTransactionNumber */
1372  const ObjectImpl<object_traits>& FetchVersion(size_t pTransactionNumber) const
1373  {
1374  if ( m_onlyMember )
1375  {
1376  tetraphilia_assert( m_map.begin()->first <= pTransactionNumber );
1377  return *m_onlyMember;
1378  }
1379 
1380  tetraphilia_assert(IsValid(pTransactionNumber));
1381 
1382  auto lIter = m_map.lower_bound(pTransactionNumber); // lIter->first >= pTransactionNumber
1383 
1384  if(lIter != m_map.end() && lIter->first == pTransactionNumber)
1385  return *lIter->second;
1386 
1387  --lIter;
1388  return *lIter->second;
1389  }

1391  const ObjectImpl<object_traits>& FetchCurrentVersion() const
1392  {
1393  if ( m_onlyMember )
1394  {
1395  tetraphilia_assert( m_map.cbegin()->first <= GetTransactionNumber() );
1396  return *m_onlyMember;
1397  }
1398 
1399  return FetchVersion(GetTransactionNumber());
1400  }

1402  bool HasVersion(size_t pTransactionNumber) const
1403  {
1404  if (m_map.empty())
1405  return false;
1406 
1407  if (m_map.find(pTransactionNumber) != m_map.end())
1408  return true;
1409  else
1410  {
1411  auto firstObjImpl = (*(m_map.cbegin())).second;
1412  if (firstObjImpl->type == kObjectTypeDictionary)
1413  {
1414  tetraphilia_assert(m_map.size() == 1);
1415  auto dictObj = firstObjImpl->u.dictAndArrayRep;
1416  if (dictObj->HasStream())
1417  return dictObj->HasVersion(pTransactionNumber);
1418  }
1419  }
1420 
1421  return false;
1422  }
1423 
1424  bool IsValid(size_t pTransactionNumber) const
1425  {
1426  if(m_map.empty())
1427  return false;
1428 
1429  if(this == &GetNullVersioner())
1430  return true;
1431 
1432  auto lIter = m_map.lower_bound(pTransactionNumber); // lIter->first >= pTransactionNumber
1433 
1434  if(lIter != m_map.end() && lIter->first == pTransactionNumber)
1435  return (lIter->second != &object_traits::GetNullObject());
1436 
1437  if(lIter == m_map.begin())
1438  return false;
1439 
1440  --lIter;
1441  return (lIter->second != &object_traits::GetNullObject());
1442  }

1524 private:
1525  void InsertInternal(size_t pTransactionNumber, const smart_ptr_type& pIDO, const ObjectImpl<object_traits>* pObjectImpl)
1526  {
1527  tetraphilia_assert(!pIDO.get() || !pIDO->IsGettingLoaded());
1528  tetraphilia_assert(!pIDO.get() || !pIDO->IsGettingConstructed());
1529 
1530  if (pIDO.get() && pIDO->IsTemporary())
1531  pTransactionNumber = 0;
1532 
1533  InvalidateStack(pTransactionNumber);
1534 
1535  auto lIter = m_map.find(pTransactionNumber);
1536  if(lIter != m_map.end())
1537  {
1538  if(pIDO.get() && !pIDO->IsTemporary() && !pIDO->IsTrailer())
1539  pIDO->GetStore()->GetObjectImplManager().Erase(pTransactionNumber, this, pIDO);
1540 
1541  m_onlyMember = nullptr;
1542  m_map.erase(lIter);
1543  }
1544 
1545  auto lPair = m_map.emplace(pTransactionNumber, pObjectImpl);
1546  tetraphilia_assert(lPair.second);
1547  m_onlyMember = ( m_map.size() == 1 ) ? lPair.first->second : nullptr;
1548 
1549  if(pIDO.get() && !pIDO->IsTemporary() && !pIDO->IsTrailer())
1550  pIDO->GetStore()->GetObjectImplManager().Insert(pTransactionNumber, this, pIDO);
1551  }
1552 
1553  void InsertInternal(size_t pTransactionNumber, IndirectObject<app_traits>& pIDO, const ObjectImpl<object_traits>* pObjectImpl)
1554  {
1555  // Trailer Dict do not have their IDO's entry in IDO cache (for xref tables). So, instead of the above variant of InsertInternal, this method gets called.
1556  tetraphilia_assert(pIDO.IsTrailer() || pIDO.IsTemporary() || pIDO.IsGettingConstructed());
1557 
1558  bool lIsGettingLoaded = pIDO.IsGettingLoaded(); // IDO being read from disk
1559 
1560  size_t lEffectiveTransactionNumber = ((lIsGettingLoaded || pIDO.IsTemporary()) ? 0 : pTransactionNumber);
1561 
1562  InvalidateStack(lEffectiveTransactionNumber);
1563 
1564  auto lIter = m_map.find(lEffectiveTransactionNumber);
1565  if(lIter != m_map.end())
1566  {
1567  if(!lIsGettingLoaded && !pIDO.IsTemporary() && !pIDO.IsTrailer())
1568  pIDO.GetStore()->GetObjectImplManager().Erase(lEffectiveTransactionNumber, this, pIDO);
1569 
1570  m_onlyMember = nullptr;
1571  m_map.erase(lIter);
1572  }
1573 
1574  auto lPair = m_map.emplace(lEffectiveTransactionNumber, pObjectImpl);
1575  tetraphilia_assert(lPair.second);
1576  m_onlyMember = ( m_map.size() == 1 ) ? lPair.first->second : nullptr;
1577 
1578  if(!lIsGettingLoaded && !pIDO.IsTemporary() && !pIDO.IsTrailer())
1579  pIDO.GetStore()->GetObjectImplManager().Insert(lEffectiveTransactionNumber, this, pIDO);
1580  }
1581 
1582  void DropTransactions(size_t pTransactionNumber)
1583  {
1584  tetraphilia_assert(pTransactionNumber != 0);
1585 
1586  if ( m_stack )
1587  m_stack->DropTransactionsNotBefore(pTransactionNumber);
1588 
1589  /* Purges all ObjectImpls created at or after version pTransactionNumber */
1590  auto lIter = m_map.lower_bound(pTransactionNumber); // lIter->first >= pTransactionNumber
1591  m_map.erase(lIter, m_map.end());
1592  m_onlyMember = ( m_map.size() == 1 ) ? m_map.begin()->second : nullptr;
1593 
1594  /* Purges all stream transactions created at or after version pTransactionNumber for a stream dictionary */
1595  if (!m_map.empty())
1596  {
1597  auto firstObjImpl = (*(m_map.cbegin())).second;
1598  if (firstObjImpl->type == kObjectTypeDictionary)
1599  {
1600  tetraphilia_assert(m_map.size() == 1);
1601  auto dictObj = firstObjImpl->u.dictAndArrayRep;
1602  if (dictObj->HasStream())
1603  dictObj->DropTransactions(pTransactionNumber);
1604  }
1605  }
1606  }
1607 
1608  void InvalidateStack( size_t pTransactionNumber )
1609  {
1610  if ( m_stack )
1611  m_stack->InvalidateVersion( pTransactionNumber );
1612  }
1613 
1614  size_t GetTransactionNumber() const
1615  {
1616  return pdf::transactions::TransactionManager::GetCurrentTransactionNumber();
1617  }
1618 
1619  heap_type& m_heap;
1620  stack_type* m_stack;
1621  allocator_type m_allocator;
1622 
1623  // Optimization: for the vast majority of cases, there will exist only one version in an
1624  // ObjectImplVersioner. If and only if m_map has exactly one member, this field will point
1625  // to that value. In all other cases this field is nullptr.
1626  const ObjectImpl<object_traits>* m_onlyMember;
1627 
1628  // Map of transaction numbers versus ObjectImpl ptrs
1629  std::map<size_t, const ObjectImpl<object_traits>*, std::less<size_t>,
1630  t4::transient_allocator<std::pair<const size_t, const ObjectImpl<object_traits>*>>> m_map;
1631 };

1880 /*
1881  The PDFObjectIteratorBase concept is specialized on a per-traits basis,
1882  and defines a subclass for PDFObjectIterator appropriate to that object
1883  traits model.
1884 
1885  It requires the following:
1886 
1887  1) A default constructor
1888  2) A constructor taking an Object<object_traits>
1889  3) A GetObject method:
1890 
1891  Object<object_traits> GetObject( bool resolve, const obj_impl_type* obj ) const
1892 
1893  GetObject must take the obj_impl_type (which may be presumed to be an
1894  element from the dictionary/array of the object with which this was constructed)
1895  and return an Object for that element.
1896 
1897  This is less straightforward than one would hope as, in the case of StoreObjTraits,
1898  an Object requires a collection of properties to properly assert its reference count
1899  and perform resolution: the IndirectObject hosting its ObjectImpl, and the Store.
1900  For ContentStreamObjTraits this is considerably simpler.
1901 
1902  Explicit specializations of PDFObjectIteratorBase may be found near the definitions
1903  of the object traits models.
1904 */
1905 template<typename object_traits>
1906 class PDFObjectIteratorBase;
1907 
1908 /*
1909  PDFObjectIterator is the workhorse class for ArrayIterator and DictionaryIterary,
1910  which are merely wrappers for this. It derives from an object-traits-specific base
1911  class which contains enough state to product valid Objects from the iteration
1912  through a raw array of ObjectImpl*'s, allowing for the possibility of reference
1913  resolution, without asserting a reference count, and thus being default constructible.
1914 */
1915 template<typename object_traits>
1916 class PDFObjectIterator : PDFObjectIteratorBase<object_traits>
1917 {
1918  friend class DictionaryIterator<object_traits, true>;
1919  friend class DictionaryIterator<object_traits, false>;
1920  friend class ArrayIterator<object_traits, true>;
1921  friend class ArrayIterator<object_traits, false>;
1922 
1923  typedef PDFObjectIteratorBase<object_traits> parent_type;
1924  typedef typename object_traits::app_traits app_traits;
1925  typedef typename object_traits::obj_impl_stack_type stack_type;
1926  typedef typename stack_type::const_iterator inner_iterator_type;
1927  typedef Object<object_traits> object_type;
1928

2651  };

2654  };

2660  to_hex( stm, *it );

2666  {
2667  assert( 0 <= d && d <= 7 );
2668  return '0' + static_cast<char>( d );
2669  };
2670 
2671  stm << "(";

2677  stm << *it;
2678  else
2679  stm << '\\' << octdigit( uch >> 6 ) << octdigit( ( uch & 0x3f ) >> 3 ) << octdigit( uch & 0x7 );
2680  }

2683  }
2684  }

2912  }

2919  };
2920  case kObjectTypeReference: {

4474 template<typename stack_type>
4475 typename stack_type::app_traits::pdf_traits::real_type PopReal( stack_type& stack )
4476 {
4477  typedef typename stack_type::app_traits::pdf_traits::real_type real_type;
4478  typedef typename stack_type::app_traits::pdf_traits::int_type int_type;
4479  real_type ret;
4480  const auto& top = stack.Top();
4481  switch ( top.type ) {
4482  default:
4483  throw t4::corrupt_data();
4484  case kObjectTypeInteger:
4485  if ( IntegerToRealConversion<int_type, real_type>::ConversionToRealWillOverflow( top.u.intRep ) )
4486  ret = top.u.intRep < 0 ? limits<real_type>::min() : limits<real_type>::max();
4487  else
4488  ret = real_type( top.u.intRep );
4489  break;
4490  case kObjectTypeLargeInteger:
4491  ret = LargeIntToRealConverter<typename stack_type::app_traits::pdf_traits::large_int_type, real_type>::Do( *top.u.largeIntRep );
4492  break;
4493  case kObjectTypeReal:
4494  ret = real_type( top.u.realRep );
4495  }
4496  stack.PopNoCheck();
4497  return ret;
4498 }

4573 template<typename app_traits>
4574 void DumpDictionaryStream( std::ostream& stm, Dictionary<StoreObjTraits<app_traits>> const& ths )
4575 {
4576  using namespace t4::literals;
4577  if ( HasStream( ths ) )
4578  {
4579  boost::io::ios_flags_saver ifs( stm );
4580  auto dbs = GetFilteredStream( ths, true );
4581  stm << "\nstream" << std::endl;
4582  data_io::BufferedDataBlockStream bds( std::move( dbs ) );
4583  static constexpr auto row_length = 16_z;
4584  while ( !bds.AtEOF() )
4585  {
4586  char const* p;
4587  auto this_row_length = std::min( row_length, bds.PeekBytes( p, row_length ) );
4588  stm << std::hex << std::setw(6) << std::setfill('0') << bds.Mark() << ' ';
4589  for ( auto i = 0_z; i < this_row_length; ++i )
4590  stm << std::hex << std::setw(2) << std::setfill('0') << static_cast<size_t>( static_cast<unsigned char>( p[i] ) ) << ' ';
4591  for ( auto i = this_row_length; i < row_length; ++i )
4592  stm << " ";
4593 
4594  stm << "| ";
4595  for ( auto i = 0_z; i < this_row_length; ++i )
4596  {
4597  if ( 32 <= p[i] )
4598  stm << p[i];
4599  else
4600  stm << '.';
4601  }
4602 
4603  stm << '\n';
4604  bds.Advance(this_row_length);
4605  }
4606 
4607  stm << "\nendstream";
4608  }
4609 }
